    public interface Disposable
    This class marks classes, which require some work done for cleaning up. As a general policy you shouldn't call the dispose() method directly, but register your object to be chained with a parent disposable via Disposer.register(Disposable, Disposable). If you're 100% sure that you should control the disposal of your object manually, do not call the dispose() method either. Use Disposer.dispose(Disposable) instead, since there might be any object registered in chain.
